Previous workshops in this series led to special issues of Multimedia Tools & Applics , and ACM / Springer Multimedia Systems Journal * * * * * The 3 rd International Workshop on Multimedia Information Systems follows upon the success of the first and second workshops in this series that was held in Arlington , VA , and West Point , NY , respectively . We plan to have a small focused workshop , consisting of participants drawn from a wide variety of disciplines ( e . g . theory , algorithms , real-time systems , networks , operating systems , graphics and visualization , databases , artificial intelligence , etc . ) , all of whom are engaged in research and development on one or more aspects of multimedia systems . We invite short papers ( max . 5 pages , double spaced , 12 point font ) on all aspects of multimedia information systems . The position papers will be collected in a proceeding volume and distributed at the Workshop GENERAL CHAIR : Elisa Bertino ( Univ . of Milano ) PROGRAM CHAIRS : Richard R .
